atomic_long_t client_obd::cl_lru_busy

# of busy LRU pages.

A page is considered busy if it's in writeback queue, or in transfer. Busy pages can't be discarded so they are not in LRU cache.

Definition at line 264 of file obd.h.

Referenced by client_obd_setup().

atomic_long_t* client_obd::cl_lru_left

# of available LRU slots left in the per-OSC cache.

Available LRU slots are shared by all OSCs of the same file system, therefore this is a pointer to cl_client_cache::ccc_lru_left.

Definition at line 260 of file obd.h.

Referenced by osc_lru_reserve(), osc_lru_shrink(), and osc_lru_unreserve().

__u64 client_obd::cl_lru_reclaim

stats: how many reclaims have happened for this client_obd.

reclaim and shrink - shrink is async, voluntarily rebalancing; reclaim is sync, initiated by IO thread when the LRU slots are in shortage.

Definition at line 276 of file obd.h.

Referenced by osc_lru_shrink().

atomic_t client_obd::cl_lru_shrinkers

# of threads are shrinking LRU cache.

To avoid contention, it's not allowed to have multiple threads shrinking LRU cache.

Definition at line 269 of file obd.h.

Referenced by client_obd_setup(), and osc_lru_shrink().

atomic_long_t client_obd::cl_unstable_count

# of unstable pages in this client_obd.

An unstable page is a page state that WRITE RPC has finished but the transaction has NOT yet committed.
